#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:382
msgid ""
"For each marriage decade, the share of those marriages that are recorded as "
"ending in divorce. Tracks how openly the tree records dissolutions over time "
"rather than the underlying historical rate."
msgstr ""
"For each marriage decade, the share of those marriages that are recorded as "
"ending in divorce. Tracks how openly the tree records dissolutions over time "
"rather than the underlying historical rate."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:459
msgid ""
"For every couple where both spouses carry a recorded date of death, the gap "
"in whole years between the two death dates lands the couple in a 5-year "
"band. The 50+ band captures the long tail. Couples where neither spouse has "
"a recorded death date are excluded — the interval is undefined without both "
"anchors."
msgstr ""
"Pro každý pár, kde oba manželé mají zaznamenané datum úmrtí, se rozdíl v "
"celých letech mezi oběma daty úmrtí zařadí do pětiletého pásma. Pásmo 50+ "
"zachycuje dlouhý ocas. Páry, kde ani jeden z manželů nemá zaznamenané datum "
"úmrtí, jsou vyloučeny. Bez obou kotev nelze interval určit."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:122
msgid ""
"For every couple where both spouses have at least one parent recorded, the "
"widget walks each spouse's ancestor tree up to four generations and "
"intersects the two sets. A non-empty intersection means the couple share at "
"least one common ancestor. That is the classic signature of cousin marriage "
"and pedigree collapse."
msgstr ""
"Pro každý pár, ve kterém má každý z manželů zaznamenaného alespoň jednoho "
"rodiče, prochází modul strom předků obou partnerů do čtyř generací a průniky "
"obou množin počítá. Neprázdný průnik znamená, že pár sdílí alespoň jednoho "
"společného předka. Jde o klasický rys sňatku mezi sestřenicemi či bratranci "
"a ahnenschwundu."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:302
msgid ""
"For every individual in the tree the widget counts how many descendants are "
"recorded below them across all generations. A descendant reached through two "
"different grandparents is counted once per ancestor. The ranking surfaces "
"the people whose branches actually carry the rest of the recorded lineage."
msgstr ""
"Pro každou osobu ve stromě modul počítá, kolik potomků je zaznamenáno pod ní "
"napříč všemi generacemi. Potomek dosažený přes dva různé prarodiče se počítá "
"jednou na předka. Pořadí ukazuje ty, jejichž větve nesou zbytek zaznamenané "
"linie."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/places.phtml:57
msgid ""
"For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that "
"appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and "
"counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT "
"and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects "
"geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is "
"across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no "
"place data at all are excluded."
msgstr ""
"For every individual the widget collects every distinct PLAC value that "
"appears on any of their level-1 events (BIRT, DEAT, BAPM, BURI, RESI, …) and "
"counts the unique places. Duplicates within the same individual (e.g. BIRT "
"and DEAT both in Hamburg) collapse to one place, so the count reflects "
"geographic mobility rather than how many events are recorded. The average is "
"across every individual with at least one PLAC sample; individuals with no "
"place data at all are excluded. The distribution on the right shows how "
"those counts split across 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 / 5+ distinct places per person — a "
"high tail signals migrant ancestors, a heavy bar at \\"

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/life-span.phtml:315
msgid ""
"For every individual with both a birth and a death date recorded, the "
"lifespan in whole years is derived. Each birth century forms one cohort and "
"is sampled at ages 0, 10, 20, up to 100 — the value at age N is the share of "
"the cohort that lived at least N years. Cohorts below 30 recorded "
"individuals are dropped because a single death would shift the curve by more "
"than three percentage points."
msgstr ""
"Pro každou osobu se zaznamenaným datem narození i úmrtí se vypočítá délka "
"života v celých letech. Každé století narození tvoří jednu kohortu, která se "
"vzorkuje ve věkových bodech 0, 10, 20 až 100. Hodnota při věku N udává podíl "
"kohorty, jenž se dožil alespoň N let. Kohorty s méně než 30 zaznamenanými "
"osobami se vynechávají, protože jediné úmrtí by jinak posunulo křivku o více "
"než tři procentní body."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/life-span.phtml:144
msgid ""
"For every individual with both a birth and a death date the widget computes "
"the number of days lived. A death within five years (1826 days) of birth "
"counts as under-5 mortality. The line groups those children by their birth "
"century so the historical decline becomes visible (typical 1700s value 30 to "
"40 percent, modern below 2 percent). Individuals with only a birth or only a "
"death date are silently excluded, since the rate cannot be determined "
"without both anchors. Per-century cohorts below 5 children are suppressed "
"because a single dead child would spike the line by more than 10 percentage "
"points."
msgstr ""
"Pro každou osobu se zaznamenaným datem narození i úmrtí se počítá délka "
"života. Úmrtí do pěti let (1826 dnů) po narození se počítá jako úmrtnost "
"dětí do 5 let. Čára seskupuje tyto děti podle století narození. Tak se "
"zviditelní historický pokles (v 18. století typicky 30 až 40 procent, dnes "
"pod 2 procenty). Osoby s pouze jedním ze dvou dat jsou vyloučeny. Bez obou "
"kotev nelze míru určit. Století s méně než 5 evidovanými dětmi se skrývají. "
"Jediné úmrtí by jinak vychýlilo čáru o více než 10 procentních bodů."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/tree-health.phtml:118
msgid ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."
msgstr ""
"For every individual, this bucket counts how many generations of descendants "
"are recorded below them in the tree. Bucket 0 = leaf (no descendants), "
"bucket N = an individual whose deepest verified descendant is N generations "
"younger."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/family.phtml:318
#, php-format
msgid ""
"For every marriage decade the bar is split into segments by the number of "
"children (0, 1, 2 … 10+). Each bar is normalised to 100 %%, so decades with "
"very different family counts can be compared side by side."
msgstr ""
"Pro každou dekádu sňatku je sloupec rozdělen na segmenty podle počtu dětí "
"(0, 1, 2 … 10+). Každý sloupec je normalizován na 100 %%, aby šlo srovnávat "
"dekády s velmi odlišným počtem rodin vedle sebe."

#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/tabs/names.phtml:120
msgid ""
"For every parent-child pair of the same sex (father / son and mother / "
"daughter) where both individuals carry a recorded given name, the widget "
"tokenises each name and counts the pair as a match when at least one token "
"appears on both sides. Order and position do not matter. The chart carries "
"one series per sex pairing on a shared X axis, so the two traditions can be "
"compared at a glance. Centuries with fewer than 10 recorded pairs are "
"suppressed independently per series because a single match would swing the "
"rate by more than 10 percentage points."
msgstr ""
"Pro každý rodičovsko-dětský pár stejného pohlaví (otec / syn a matka / "
"dcera), kde oba jedinci mají zaznamenané křestní jméno, modul rozdělí každé "
"jméno na tokeny a pár se počítá jako shoda, pokud se alespoň jeden token "
"objeví na obou stranách. Pořadí ani pozice nezáleží. Graf nese jednu sérii "
"na pohlavní pár na společné ose X, aby bylo možné obě tradice porovnat na "
"první pohled. Století s méně než 10 zaznamenanými páry jsou potlačena "
"nezávisle pro každou sérii, protože jediná shoda by změnila míru o více než "
"10 procentních bodů."

